docs.abstract: The University of Virginia in Charlottesville, designed by Thomas Jefferson, was built by enslaved people. The Memorial to Enslaved Laborers acknowledges that long-suppressed history.
docs.snippet: The University of Virginia in Charlottesville, designed by Thomas Jefferson, was built by enslaved people. The Memorial to Enslaved Laborers acknowledges that long-suppressed history.
docs.lead_paragraph: CHARLOTTESVILLE, Va. — “Can we forget the crack of the whip, cowhide, whipping-post, the auction-block, the hand-cuffs, the spaniels, the iron collar, the negro-trader tearing the young child from its mother’s breast as a whelp from the lioness? Have we forgotten that by these horrible cruelties, hundreds of our race have been killed? No, we have not, or ever will.”

headline.main: Turning Grief for a Hidden Past Into a Healing Space
headline.print_headline: Where ‘Horrible Cruelties’ Can No Longer Hide

docs.abstract: He led The Detroit Free Press at 33, then gave up journalism for Hollywood. “Absence of Malice” was one result; an Oscar for “Out of Africa” was another.
docs.snippet: He led The Detroit Free Press at 33, then gave up journalism for Hollywood. “Absence of Malice” was one result; an Oscar for “Out of Africa” was another.
docs.lead_paragraph: Kurt Luedtke, a former newspaper executive who forged a successful second career writing Hollywood screenplays, notably for “Absence of Malice” and the Oscar-winning “Out of Africa,” died on Sunday at a hospital in Royal Oak, Mich. He was 80.

headline.main: Kurt Luedtke, Newspaperman Turned Screenwriter, Dies at 80
headline.print_headline: Kurt Luedtke, 80, Newspaper Executive Turned Hollywood Screenwriter, Dies

docs.abstract: A television critic and a fashion critic discuss what they saw, what they learned and what it could mean for the future.
docs.snippet: A television critic and a fashion critic discuss what they saw, what they learned and what it could mean for the future.
docs.lead_paragraph: The largely virtual format of the Republican and Democratic national conventions meant that even more than usual, the messages were embedded within the visual presentation. Here Vanessa Friedman, the chief fashion critic for The New York Times, and James Poniewozik, the chief television critic, discuss what they saw and what it all meant.

headline.main: The 2020 Party Conventions Gave New Meaning to Political Theater

docs.abstract: Ms. Omar, a member of the “Squad” of progressive women of color elected to the House two years ago, topped a well-funded challenger in a victory for the left.
docs.snippet: Ms. Omar, a member of the “Squad” of progressive women of color elected to the House two years ago, topped a well-funded challenger in a victory for the left.
docs.lead_paragraph: MINNEAPOLIS — Representative Ilhan Omar of Minnesota fended off a well-funded primary challenger on Tuesday, ensuring a clean sweep of re-election fights for the group of first-term Democratic congresswomen of color known as the Squad and sending a message to Washington about the staying power of the party’s new progressive voices.

headline.main: Ilhan Omar Wins House Primary in Minnesota

docs.abstract: Kaatsbaan hosts a welcome summer festival in the Hudson Valley, where nature and dancers join forces to put on a show.
docs.snippet: Kaatsbaan hosts a welcome summer festival in the Hudson Valley, where nature and dancers join forces to put on a show.
docs.lead_paragraph: TIVOLI, N.Y. — It didn’t bode well that the first live dance I was going to see since mid-March was one I had seen many times before. “Sunshine,” a Larry Keigwin war horse set to the Bill Withers’s classic “Ain’t No Sunshine,” can give a dancer the opportunity to really feel the music in all the worst ways. It’s treacly stuff.

headline.main: What Is It Like to Watch Live Dance Again? Amazing
headline.print_headline: A Reminder That Live Dance Is Amazing

docs.abstract: The Alvin Ailey artistic director is hunkered down in Connecticut, tending his vegetable garden and keeping his mood aloft with these 10 essentials.
docs.snippet: The Alvin Ailey artistic director is hunkered down in Connecticut, tending his vegetable garden and keeping his mood aloft with these 10 essentials.
docs.lead_paragraph: “I always say that pessimism and anger is a place that I visit, but my permanent address is optimism and hope,” said Robert Battle, the artistic director of Alvin Ailey American Dance Theater. And this year he’s done plenty of traveling back and forth.

headline.main: Robert Battle Keeps Going With Sarah Vaughan and Homegrown Tomatoes
headline.print_headline: Robert Battle Likes to Cook, and Connect

docs.lead_paragraph: Chadwick Boseman, the regal actor who embodied a long-held dream of African-American moviegoers as the star of the groundbreaking superhero film “Black Panther,” died on Friday at his home in Los Angeles. He was 43.
